{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the meanwhile, trying to get visas was virtually impossible because there was nowhere to get / my father was still trying to get out through Genoa because Italy was in the war, but there was still a way to get out and America was neutral at that time.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So the American consulate was still there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But-- because America had not declared a war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But it was totally impossible to get out, so we sat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it became very nerve-racking to have these seven adults-- no five adults and the two children-- sitting there, nothing to do.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Also, since the synagogue burned down, they had hired a hall near the synagogue where us children would go every day for schooling, schooling in quotation marks.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It would be mothers who knew a little bit more than others who would teach us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then once a week, a rabbi from another town would come and give us religious training.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This was five days a week.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And by this time, there were one two, three, four, five, six, maybe 10 children left in town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This continued through 1939 and it continued on until we left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The school was situated such a way that every day we had to walk past our burned out synagogue.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was-- made t doubly hard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But anyway.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When did you leave Speyer?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How did that come about?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On November-- October 22nd, 1940, the war had been going on for a year.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Holland had been invaded, France had been conquered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Early in the morning, about four o'clock in the morning, the doorbell rang, someone banging on the doors, open up, open up and once.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My cousin and I were sleeping in my room, which had been our den before.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
